From dd8efefee6d0b478aaaa739db5e583636c01d5e9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 30 May 2026 18:15:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 9/9] arm64: configs: sdm845: enable Mi 8 (dipper) driver
 modules

Enable the driver modules required by sdm845-xiaomi-dipper.dts:

  - TOUCHSCREEN_STM_FTS_DOWNSTREAM for the FTM5 touchscreen
  - DRM_PANEL_SAMSUNG_EA8074 for the Mi 8 AMOLED panel
  - VIDEO_OV7251 for the front-IR sensor (required by qcom-camss
    async-binding even when streaming is not used)
  - SND_SOC_TAS2557 for the speaker amplifier

All four are built as modules; they are only loaded when the matching
DT node is present, so peer sdm845 boards keep their current behaviour.

Signed-off-by: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm64/configs/sdm845_defconfig | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/configs/sdm845_defconfig b/arch/arm64/configs/sdm845_defconfig
index 78b6b0bc7..9400196ab 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/configs/sdm845_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm64/configs/sdm845_defconfig
@@ -1,3 +1,7 @@
+CONFIG_TOUCHSCREEN_STM_FTS_DOWNSTREAM=m
+CONFIG_DRM_PANEL_SAMSUNG_EA8074=m
+CONFIG_VIDEO_OV7251=m
+CONFIG_SND_SOC_TAS2557=m
 CONFIG_SYSVIPC=y
 CONFIG_POSIX_MQUEUE=y
 CONFIG_AUDIT=y
-- 
